# 🌤️ Weather Max Temperature Predictor

This is a **Streamlit web application** that predicts the **maximum daily temperature** based on current weather conditions using a machine learning model (XGBoost Regressor).

> 🔗 Live App: [Click here to launch](https://streamlit.io/cloud)

---

## 🚀 Features

- Predicts max temperature (°C) based on:
  - Rainfall
  - Humidity (9am & 3pm)
  - Pressure (9am & 3pm)
  - Temperature (9am & 3pm)
  - Rain status
  - Wind direction
- Built with **XGBoost** trained on historical weather data
- Interactive UI using **Streamlit**

---

## 📊 Input Parameters

| Feature         | Type     | Description                            |
|-----------------|----------|----------------------------------------|
| Rainfall        | Numeric  | Rainfall in mm                         |
| Humidity9am     | Slider   | Humidity at 9am (%)                    |
| Humidity3pm     | Slider   | Humidity at 3pm (%)                    |
| Pressure9am     | Numeric  | Atmospheric pressure at 9am (hPa)      |
| Pressure3pm     | Numeric  | Atmospheric pressure at 3pm (hPa)      |
| Temp9am         | Slider   | Temperature at 9am (°C)                |
| Temp3pm         | Slider   | Temperature at 3pm (°C)                |
| RainToday       | Select   | Whether it rained today                |
| WindDir3pm      | Select   | Wind direction at 3pm (categorical)    |

---

## 🧠 Model

- **Algorithm**: XGBoost Regressor
- **Training**: Model trained on cleaned and preprocessed weather data
- **File**: `xgb_model.json` (included in the repo)

---

## 📦 Installation & Run Locally

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/weather-temp-predictor.git
cd weather-temp-predictor

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run the Streamlit app
streamlit run app.py
